{"id":"grape","term":"Grape","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The fruit of the vine, which was extensively cultivated in Palestine. Grapes are spoken of as “tender” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Song of Solomon 2:13\">Cant. 2:13</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Song of Solomon 2:15\">15</a>), “unripe” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Job 15:33\">Job 15:33</a>), “sour” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 18:5\">Isa. 18:5</a>), “wild” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 5:2\">Isa. 5:2</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 5:4\">4</a>). (See <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 14:18\">Rev. 14:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Micah 7:1\">Micah 7:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 6:9\">Jer. 6:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 18:2\">Ezek. 18:2</a>, for figurative use of the word.) (See VINE.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Song of Solomon 2:13","Song of Solomon 2:15","Job 15:33","Isaiah 18:5","Isaiah 5:2","Isaiah 5:4","Revelation 14:18","Micah 7:1","Jeremiah 6:9","Ezekiel 18:2"]}